A new era of crisis begins.
France and the rest of Europe are in the sights of investors.
A tornado of statistics passed over Europe on Tuesday.
Each of the states has published GDP information for the 3As.
The Czech economy has stagnated this last quarter, while France and Germany are growing.
The bond market is breaking all records.
Investors are not just looking at Italy, but also Spain, France, Austria and others.
Statistical offices in the Eurozone, Germany, Czechia and other European countries released earlier their views on economic development for the third quarter.
Germany&#39;s GDP is expected to grow by 0.5%, France&#39;s by 0.4%.
Both countries changed the data for the second quarter in which Germany performed better than expected (0.3% growth instead of the 0.1% expected), however France reported a slight decrease of 0.1% (it was originally a question of stagnation).
The Czech economy grew by 1.5% in the third quarter.
But GDP has stagnated and according to the Czech Statistical Office it is confirmed that we are heading for a gradual decrease in economic growth.
