The Czech economy grew by 1.5% during the third quarter but stagnated during the last quarter.
The German economy had in the third quarter a growth of 0.5% according to the data forecast and periodically recalculated.
The economy of the eurozone and the European Union grew by 0.2% between July and September compared to the previous quarter, which is in line with what analysts had expected.
The Greek economy fell by 5.2%.
