Feeding an obese child: do not eat breakfast and eat cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren are overweight and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows again how important is the environment in which the human being evolves and the models which surround him.
On the tables of obese children, for example, meats are found 50% more often than in families with children of normal weight.
19% of obese people had fries for dinner according to the survey carried out with an awareness campaign &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot;
Sport is also not a habit in the families of the little fat children, which is now the case for most school children today - only 15% answered that at least once a week the parents find the time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 pupils from primary schools in the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot;, action supported by the General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third grade have signed up for this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight and even obese children is the absence of a correct diet and not enough physical exercise.
&quot;Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - snack-dinner, which is one of the basic principles of a good diet&quot;, indicates one of the results of the study. &#39;investigation.
Without breakfast and charcuterie at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that healthy development requires a few basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of student families eat at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst that has been noted is that a tenth of the population does not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that families with obese children eat unhealthy fries more often.
Almost every student - not to mention the weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned play sports regularly but for the parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food from the possibilities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
&quot;The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from the ideal in terms of healthy food&quot;.
Among their favorite dishes are many cakes, meats and sweets.
&quot;The most alarming thing is notably a great preference for sweet lemonades&quot;, is stated in the results of the survey.
For lunch, pasta took first place just ahead of white meat.
The children did not want any starches at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Heading for health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive ad hoc information.
&quot;During a control of a group of participants in the survey who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot;, we witnessed a very determined desire to move towards an healthy eating,&quot; say the survey results.
The most striking was, for example, with regard to sweet lemonades because the children began to give preference to drinking water.
The children most often ticked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as main course and would reduce sweet dishes and &quot;knedliky&quot; (Czech specialty of bread flour or potato dumplings).
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say the professionals
In an overview article about how to learn for stylists, I got a little angry that there were a lot of them early on.
I didn&#39;t think about what was going to happen next.
The presentations of three professionals of the specialty, the clothing of the characters and a seminar on what happens on site.
And it will be worse.
The closer we get to the final exams, the more practical exercises and information await us.
And even when there are classes on Saturdays and Sundays, it&#39;s really &quot;crammed&quot;.
This time we have with the director Alenka (in the course there are no boys) dealt with how to dress the woman who does not have standard measurements.
And women of this type are the majority.
One has a small neck, the other a boy&#39;s body, without any particular curve, another is overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically reduce wide arms, extend a neck or add necessary curves.
We managed to emphasize the character nicely and also not to dress too showy types of women like Jennifer Lopez with a large chest and pronounced hips and a thin waist.
If, for example, there is a difference between the waist and the hips in such a way that the skirts or trousers do not fit at all, it is worth having it made to measure.
And you won&#39;t regret it because clothing that fits impeccably is priceless.
In a made-to-measure skirt you will feel much better than in one that constantly slips, rolls up and does not fit on the belt and so on.
For those who have a masculine appearance, they can afford Tucker-style clothing, with pieces of sewn fabric, or even embroidery.
There are obviously a lot of examples of various appearances and I&#39;m glad I have all week to sort through all the information received.
But I&#39;m also afraid that for what I have to do at home there is too much.
Each trainee was given a celebrity to dress for the day and evening.
We have to take into consideration the current appearance, personality mode type as well as appearance.
I will have to &quot;dress&quot; Miranda Kerr, who you may know from the Victoria&#39;s Secret campaign.
Deep down, I&#39;m happy because it&#39;s better than dressing Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera who has gained almost a hundred pounds lately (please don&#39;t take my statement completely seriously) or the young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut and sew from magazines or search the internet, print and work on the design.
The Moodboard, as we say for the final result, expresses our personal style as well as our relationship with graphic design.
Also thinking about the graphic part of the styling is also important.
The stylist does not only dress the physique in this way but creates for example productive pages in magazines (on given products the trends for handbags, coats, etc...).
Mario Kamenik, stylist and graphic designer, told us all about it.
But this...until Sunday
The stylist must have a general vision
Three specialty guests gave a diverse look to Saturday&#39;s session filled with information about the different character types.
Honza Pokorny, stylist, Jakub Polanka fashion designer and Ben Renc, fashion photographer.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to use it.
And a talented stylist knows how to work with one piece of clothing in a different way.
Variability is essential for this example.
Like for example this trench coat which must be worn in a classic way with jeans and a t-shirt like a light coat but also it can also dress the naked body, with pumps and take a picture of it like a dress .
Or just roll up the sleeves or the collar and immediately have a new look.
&quot;Play with it&quot; he stressed.
But I particularly appreciated the following advice: &quot;For work you need to know the rules perfectly&quot;.
&quot;You can then start violating it,&quot; Jakub said.
Finally I understand why we strive to learn these rules, what to do with them, towards what, why, whereas in fashion magazines we sometimes see something else.
No statement on fashion shows.
I know again, thanks to fashion photographer Ben, that the stylist must have many more variations of clothing than are photographed.
That is to say that for a fashion story which will have about ten pages (so about ten models) I must be ready to &quot;recut&quot; at least fifteen.
And also, a piece of clothing and its combination with other elements appear completely differently than in reality.
We have to reckon with this during a creation of a model.
The fact that image and style are sometimes half the success was confirmed to us by Honza Pokorny.
Just look at Madonna who is not a super singer but her image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the approach to using the services of stylists is still cautious.
And known faces sometimes consider them useless (it is enough that I know something but what I seem comes second).
And if someone gets a styling done from us, then we have to rely on the fact that they dictate to us with a high probability a completely different (smaller) size than they actually have.
Then we just have to browse on google and make sure if the boulevard info mentions the celebrity in question, if she has lost weight or gained weight etc...
Honza and Mario asked us Sunday on the heart that it is not enough for the stylist to orient himself in fashion and know how to assemble models.
He must communicate with the people he dresses and it is therefore important to be a good psychologist.
Knowing how to guess people, not flattering yourself, keeping your opinion.
&quot;When a manager asks you to sort out her closet and fill it with new items, you can&#39;t just throw it all away and tell her, My God, how awful.&quot;
&quot;You&#39;ll find a few things that you think are pretty and he&#39;ll advise you what to wear them with,&quot; Mario says.
This one showed us concretely what must all contain what is called the &quot;placovka&quot; or stylist&#39;s bag.
It&#39;s the one you hang around your waist and carry around for everything you need.
In addition to clearly defined things such as scissors, rollers for depilation or even safety pins, there are also nylon thread (which the stylist uses to photograph products such as bags, or hats), clips specials with which to close a garment in the back, if it is too big (the pin or other type of staple cannot be used because they could damage the garment) or a sewing kit.
So that we weren&#39;t just people who listened but tried something in a practical way, they taught us how to resole shoes properly.
And during the photo session in the workshop where the surface is even, the sole could be damaged, especially on the outside.
And so we glued and glued.
We were not allowed to touch the scissors so as not to inadvertently hurt ourselves.
So you really need skills.
Mario made me happy when he congratulated me on my creation.
The skill I am reporting is not for my girlfriend.
This is only a small summary of what we learned during the second weekend of classes
I am beginning to understand more and more that making styling a profession is not a walk in a rose garden, let everyone say what they want.
The need for speed The Run is disputed across America.
Revision
From a trouble-free run, a series of stupid mistakes by people who don&#39;t care turns into a routine morning trip to work.
It satisfies everyone&#39;s ambition to a certain extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new part subtitled The Run produced high expectations ahead of its release.
It promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and release a kind of game from the playable parts that wouldn&#39;t just be counted with points.
We were therefore curious how the added passages will be during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
They are potentially arcade racing games but the whole thing drags down because of some unnecessary faults that have already existed for several years.
These are not really errors but rather an expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are taken in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race is done on a different route and the stages planned in different environments which are quite distinct from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are moreover quite pretty even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Finally it is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snow-capped mountains is very pleasing visually.
The proofs are also from time to time embellished with an atypical element.
For example in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm which significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Besides that, the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few, but that&#39;s enough.
There are moments you strive to overcome the requested number of opponents (like in a classic race) then you will race against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police come into play and try to make things difficult for you.
New are the out-of-vehicle passages.
It&#39;s more of an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What&#39;s surprising is that there are fewer such moments than you&#39;d expect (to be concrete there are only three).
With the result it is good like that because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements which decorate the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that currently there is nothing extraordinary but we cannot say that it is negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to look elsewhere.
But although you can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems start to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet developed.
We don&#39;t expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you don&#39;t have any idea when colliding with any object how your auto behaves, it&#39;s not is therefore not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other lightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy aerobatics.
Or else finds itself in pieces.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your face or you have gone out into the scenery, the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 reboots.
When you have used all 5 restarts you must restart the game from the beginning.
So it&#39;s more of a tool, in case something goes wrong, than something you can actually rely on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by recalling from memory the piece of route in question.
The big problem with this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain bends that you have to pass in a certain way otherwise it won&#39;t pass.
Otherwise you will encounter &quot;civilian&quot; vehicles in a given location, always in the same configuration whether you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent pass easily between two oncoming cars and when you arrive, you have to either step aside and go around them or brake.
It doesn&#39;t matter if you go in front of him because it is &quot;calculated&quot; in such a way that for the given situation he always comes close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages as well.
During the whole time of the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent who precedes you in the same place.
This irritates the most in the late game when you&#39;re rolling over a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The adversary must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it blocks the view of other oncoming vehicles and you collide a lot of times.
We can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it&#39;s a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you don&#39;t have time to follow everything that happens.
And it does not matter if it is because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You must pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there, however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for city driving, American muscle cars for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic trappings for highly technical driving such as winding roads in the mountains.
And the challenges mode, which are races in particular locations that you know from the adventure, goes really well with the main story scheme.
You not only receive medals but also experience points which are added to your profile which is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest driver level, different items begin to unlock:
This connects on-line with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results obtained with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speedometer tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you comes a metro train that sends the car straight to the scrapyard.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days to know if someone really thought during the creation of this game or if the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not great, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What bothers is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold up, and in some cases tragically so.
This especially concerns crashes with a large number of participants when smooth imagery is no longer of any use to you.
The sound part is good and the track is your choice.
In order to appeal to as many people as possible and especially to young audiences a new soundtrack has been created in the style &quot;I mix everything&quot;, but it can be expected that no one will buy the game for the music .
Overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game didn&#39;t have these stupid errors we could safely say that this is NFS&#39; best production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for the fouls to smack you in the eye with the force of an airfield reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival, 20 choirs from upper and secondary schools perform.
The highlight of the festival is formed by two concerts organized on November 17th.
&quot;Charles University has an important part in this festival&quot;.
“Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl”, indicates the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of high schools and secondary classes which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening, the &quot;Students of Velvet&quot; concert takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University perform.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate International Students&#39; Day with dignity and remember the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choir music of the highest level to the public and develop creative cooperation among young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Singers in cooperation with the Jan Kepler Lyceum.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20 in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, musical encounters, a student happening and other activities.
Those interested will find all the information on the festival&#39;s internet pages www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
&quot;The Treaty of Lisbon has radically removed the balance between the institutions&quot;
&quot;I did not expect such a harsh war&quot;.
&quot;It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role&quot;, this is how Miléna Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she succeeded in describing the different bodies of the EU and their relationships so clearly and visibly that many lecturers at Charles University Law School would envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her &quot;understandable and open about Europe&quot; motto.
Mrs Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
&quot;Right from the start there were the criticisms that he&#39;s bland, he&#39;s a piece of cake, he can&#39;t do any job and I have to say he took everyone&#39;s breath away because he holds his role to perfection.
&quot;He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicates well with them and has a clear vision of the direction Europe should take&quot;.
She explained the new post of High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defense Policy as part of an answer to the question: &quot;Who is who in the European Union?&quot; &quot;Which telephone number should I call?&quot;, therefore as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater clarity of the Union&#39;s policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban us from our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She described the Czech Presidency two years ago as a success.
The Czechs solved the growing financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized an Eastern Partnership Summit.
She described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, &quot;activity was in full swing&quot; not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis which continues to resolve even now.
It is also necessary to approve the new seventh budget of the Union which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it would seem that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the framework of future negotiations.
Madam Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels &quot;For an understandable Europe&quot;.
&quot;I really don&#39;t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand that it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted gherkins, differently large bananas or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky&quot;.
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in EU institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative rather than positive aspects.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault results, according to her, from several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad group.
&quot;Believe me, when the Poles, the Magyars, the Slovaks come towards me, this Frenchman says to me: &#39;Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?&#39; at all happy&quot;.
According to Ms. Vicenova, in the near future, new tough rules in terms of budgetary policy await member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed one, which prevails rather than a &quot;new European Federation&quot;.
&quot;We have countries in the euro zone and others outside the zone.&quot;
&quot;We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation&quot;.
In the first place, it was said that the countries which want it cooperate with each other and those which do not want it stay in their corner.
&quot;There will be many institutes of this type and there will be a really two-speed Europe&quot;, expects Mrs Vicenova.
From this point of view she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and of Herman Van Rompuye to determine the bases according to which all the topics having an impact on the EU must be discussed between all the members of the EU and not only members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
The IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone had to look for the term that most closely expresses IBM&#39;s strategy, the closest would be &quot;the long term&quot;.
For a large public IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt to be very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm&#39;s first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that many of the world&#39;s problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
Its slogan &quot;THINK!&quot; has become the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
This was the foundation of Watson&#39;s carefully crafted corporate culture.
For us IBM means long-term thinking of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM has survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained faithful to its basic values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
