The Court validates &quot;the analog cut&quot; in Mexico in 2015
The substitution of analogical signals by digital ones is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered in the last years.
The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional controversies that the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies formulated against the presidential decree which advances the so-called &quot;analog cut&quot; from 2021 to 2015, because the eight votes necessary for the &#39;invalidate have not been met.
A minority of four ministers, including the President of the Court, Juan Silva Meza, considered that President Felipe Calderón did not exceed his powers when he issued the decree which details the actions to be taken to make the transition a reality. on digital terrestrial television.
With this result, the constitutional controversy promoted by the Senate of the Republic, was dismissed for not having reached the qualified majority of eight votes for the Court to decide on the constitutionality or non-constitutionality of the decree, and this continues to be in force.
The draft sentence, drawn up by the Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, proposed the declaration of the decree as unconstitutional, because the regulation in the matter of radio and television is an attribution reserved by law to the Federal Telecommunications Commission ( Cofetel), in contravention of the principles of hierarchical subordination and reserve of law.
In favor of the project only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero voted.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies promoted two constitutional controversies to contest the decree and admitting the complaints, Minister Sánchez Cordero suspended the application of the decree and of all the actions foreseen by it for the digital transformation.
The plenary session of the ministers resolved to reject also the complaint formulated by the Chamber of Deputies, without discussing the project for which the minister Sánchez Cordero is also responsible.
In his speech, the Minister President said that he did not agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the Federal Executive cannot structure through general norms the measures so that the public administration prepare for it.
&quot;Nor do I consider that if he did so, the autonomy of the regulatory body would be affected&quot;, and he recalled that the planning of public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of the &#39;Federal executive, which has the constitutional mandate of running the state.
The substitution of analogue signals by digital signals is one of the most important changes that the world has undergone in recent years and this translates into better use of the radio spectrum, better signal quality and more channels.
Postponing change, he argued, would be postponing the benefits of digitalization which involves a decision of public interest that does not only have a technical dimension, &quot;because it also includes economic, social, political and national security&quot;.
These issues, he stressed, &quot;require the operation of a whole system established, in accordance with the principle of economic management of the State, encompasses a group of attributions that the Constitution grants to the faculty of the Executive to the state&quot;.
He recalled that a large number of countries all over the world have already finished the digital transition and they have done it through the Executive, despite the fact that they had highly specialized technical bodies.
It cannot be concluded that the Executive, by issuing the contested decree, has invaded in any way the sphere of competence of Congress, because it ensures in the administrative sphere compliance with the laws issued by the Legislative, he assured .
We analyze the possibility of a &quot;vote by vote&quot; count in Michoacán
According to the data highlighted by PREP, the difference between first and second place in the gubernatorial election is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to the 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
The possibility of &quot;vote by vote&quot; counting is a reality with regard to the electoral process this year in Michoacán, where according to data highlighted by the Preliminary Electoral Results Program (PREP) the difference between first and second place of the gubernatorial election is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to the 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
In this sense, the president of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, last November 9, the electoral body approved a series guidelines to harmonize local standards with federal electoral reform.
It will be remembered that Michoacán did not approve either its Political Constitution or its State Electoral Code or its Law of Electoral Justice, at the same time that the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal term. for this electoral process to enter into force and the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted its publication within the deadlines provided for by the Law of the Official Gazette of the State, with the argument that he had some objections.
On the same November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Legislative Power and qualified as &quot;invalid and illegal&quot; the vote of the state agent for the constitutional reforms, because he has no right to &quot;sanction or challenge&quot; them.
Interviewed on the possibility of &quot;vote by vote&quot;, María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to carry out the partial and total counts of the votes by the body local election.
Thus, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, it is possible that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there are no minutes of the ballot and count in the file of the ballot box is not with the president thereof; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the votes received in all the ballot boxes of the election may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the candidate presumed winner of the respective election and the one who obtained the second place in the ballot is equal or below a point of percentage; whenever at the beginning of the session an express petition of the representative of the party and/or coalition exists that presented/displayed the second of the indicated candidates.
The total count of the vote can also be carried out if at the end of the common count it turns out that the difference between the supposed winning candidate and that of the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express petition from the representative of the political party whose candidate came out second, in which case the electoral packages that were subject to the partial count will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that this is the situation of the Morelia election, where according to the PREP, the difference between first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the total 923 minutes.
