The &quot;framework is now well drawn&quot;, he added.
Monti completed the process to form a government in less than three days, in less than normal time, as Italy battles a political and financial crisis that has pushed its debt costs to unsustainable levels.
The new administration led by former European Commissioner Monti must approve a harsh austerity package demanded by European leaders to recover the confidence in Italy that had been affected.
Underscoring the pressure on Monti to hurry, market volatility pushed the yield on Italy&#39;s 10-year BTP bonds above 7 percent, the level Greece and Ireland must have been at. saved.
