The municipal competition on the 16 doors reopens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the already extinct Metropolitan Corporation of Barcelona (CMB), this Administration printed posters promoting Collserola.
The brochure defined the mountain as the great park of metropolitan Barcelona.
In addition, it also contained a comparison, in figures, with New York&#39;s Central Park.
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park again became, in the imagination of many people, the upper limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital being the only one that does not orient itself on the north-eastern axis. south, otherwise high (mountain) - low (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park is to the advantage of this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park if not Yellowstone, with wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
This was the situation until, in September, the town hall called a mega-competition made up of 16 competitions for all the access doors to Collserola.
A gate brings back the park idea, definitely.
That&#39;s it, or someone wants to put doors in the field.
The question arises by itself: Collserola: park or mountain?
The competition, both in terms of its organization and in terms of reflection on the city, is a topic of conversation for all architects in Barcelona.
It&#39;s almost a recurring theme that two members of this ancient chosen caste talk about when they recognize each other in an elevator.
And this is precisely one of the rare opinions on which three architects from Barcelona, university professors, who presented themselves there coincide.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the competition is timely.
For Roldán, after approaching the coastal front &quot;it is necessary to&quot; debate on &quot;the mountain front&quot; because the speech of Ildefons Cerda, that of the green blocks of houses has not been completed.
&quot;You have to start from the base that the largest park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things for its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex&quot;, gave the verdict the architect for whom the title of &quot;Doors of Collserola&quot; contains a &quot;lexical trap&quot;: these should not be thought of &quot;as the accesses to a park, but the delimitation of certain areas in which action is needed&quot;.
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, qualifies the proposal as an &quot;intellectual challenge&quot; with &quot;some perils&quot;.
Perils that derive from &quot;the uncertainty of the projection of the public space&quot; after the experience lived in the 80s and which had in the area of the Forum &quot;its swan song&quot;.
The first fear is the own delimitation of the borders on which one can build.
&quot;To limit something means to already establish the next step&quot;, that is to say, its overcoming.
&quot;We must think of new urban planning instruments, because the current ones [in reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)] can cause real disasters&quot;.
Sticking more to the question, Modol opines that, simplifying, the slope of the El Valles de Collserola region &quot;can be understood as a park, that of Barcelona, no&quot;.
Modol recalls that there is already work done by the Patronage of Collserola which &quot;must not be lost&quot;, thanking for the opportunity that the town hall offers to its corporation to intervene in this project &quot;from the first moment&quot;.
In addition, he hears that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the safe-conduct that allows architects to enter into the debate, but &quot;doubts&quot; if this technical profile should lead the multidisciplinary teams (&quot;quite a success&quot;, he says) that we had to create: &quot;We, the architects, should be only an instrument&quot;.
Bayona insinuates that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, because the bases of the competition lack a global vision of Collserola: &quot;16 transversal competitions have been called - he says - in the mountain sense- sea, but there is no longitudinal reading that sees and understands the area as a whole&quot;.
This makes, at least in this case, that he opted to participate in the 16 contests.
Alternatively, a project for one of the doors can clash in program and definition with that of the architect of the neighboring door.
In his opinion, yes, the town hall should guarantee that the strip immediately above that of Ronda de Dalt should provide, in all its extension, an area of equipment that makes a smooth transition between the city and the green.
Casino forgives Jonás Larrazábal and he will be released
After 72 days of provisional arrest, the legal attorney of Casino Red has granted a pardon to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey for the lawsuit initiated against him for alleged blackmail
After spending 72 years arrested, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the legal attorney of Casino Red grants him a pardon in the Second District Criminal Court, which is following a blackmail trial against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the Casino Royale bombing, the owner of Casino Red, Sergio Gil García, published a series of photos and videos in which Manuel Jonás allegedly demanded payment of an economic quota from him so that the mayor of Monterrey allowed the clandestine operation of the gambling house.
After the public denunciation, the Public Prosecutor&#39;s Office opened a criminal trial against the brother of the PANist mayor and on September 2, he was arrested and held in provisional arrest for 30 days.
After four hours before Public Prosecution Officer 3 of Patrimonial Offenses, he was transferred to Detention Center 1, located in the Old Quarter of the state capital.
He remained there for the next 49 days when he was given a second detention order after the Public Prosecutor dismissed the charges of corruption and organized crime.
On October 19 he was transferred to the Penal Center of Cadereyta presumably for having blackmailed the owners of Casino Red with one and a half million pesos; but he only spent a few hours in the medium security detention center because there were death threats against him.
The authorities allowed him to continue the trial confined in the municipal cells of San Nicolás de los Garza.
On October 25, a capture order was issued by the clerk of the Second District Criminal Court, Jorge Yánez, who said that after almost two months of investigation there was sufficient confirmed evidence to determine Jonás&#39; guilt, such as that relating to the collection of 1.5 million pesos from the representatives of the gambling house in exchange for allowing its operation.
This Monday, the legal representative of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, appeared before the judge José Luis Pecina to request a pardon for the brother of the mayor of the region; therefore he could recover his freedom within the next few hours.
During the legal formalities, the agent of the Public Ministry attached to the Court, Ramiro Arias, questioned García Gómez if the damage had been recovered and which of the associates of the gambling house had been the one who had granted the pardon, but the lawyer tried not to release the name.
By virtue of the file 197/2011 the legal pardon is granted to Jonás Larrazábal and subsequently no claim can be made in relation to the lawsuit brought against him; he will not be asked for any compensation for damages and no punishment either.
After the hearing of the legal representative of the gambling house, at 3:50 pm the immediate release of Larrazabal Bretón was ordered.
The court clerk, Jorge Yánez, went to the prison of the municipality of San Nicolás de los Garza to inform Jonás that he had been legally pardoned and his case would be closed.
He will also communicate to him the order of immediate release that the judge has issued.
